                            <comment id="13025394" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 26 Apr 2011 19:38:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like in the Big Gossip Refactor there was a slight regression.  We avoid notifying if there&apos;s not a major state change, however we also need to see if the node was previously dead and if so, notify.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13025450" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 26 Apr 2011 21:32:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13025472" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 26 Apr 2011 22:12:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13025501" author="hudson" created="Tue, 26 Apr 2011 22:56:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra-0.8 #43 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.8/43/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.8/43/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    Mark nodes that were previously down as alive, even without a major&lt;br/&gt;
state change.&lt;br/&gt;
